# Solver Theory

The organizing identity is

\[
n = z^3 + dN(x-y\omega)
\]

with

\[
\omega = \frac{-1+\sqrt{-3}}{2}
\]

and

\[
N(x-y\omega)=x^2-xy+y^2=q.
\]

Using

\[
d=x+y,\qquad s=x-y
\]

the shell equation becomes

\[
4q=d^2+3s^2
\]

and the cubic transport equation becomes

\[
4(n-z^3)=d^3+3ds^2.
\]

A candidate is valid only when the exact square condition

\[
\Delta = \frac{4q-d^2}{3}=s^2
\]

holds and reconstruction gives integers

\[
x=\frac{d+s}{2},\qquad y=\frac{d-s}{2}
\]

with

\[
x^3+y^3+z^3=n.
\]

